nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.simulators

Interface DEVSSimulatorInterface<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the extended type itself to be able to implement a comparator on the simulation time.
    All Superinterfaces:
    nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducerInterface, java.rmi.Remote, java.io.Serializable, SimulatorInterface<A,R,T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DEVDESSSimulatorInterface<A,R,T>, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.CalendarDouble, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.CalendarFloat, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.CalendarLong, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.TimeDouble, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.TimeFloat, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.TimeFloatUnit, DEVDESSSimulatorInterface.TimeLong, DEVSSimulatorInterface.CalendarDouble, DEVSSimulatorInterface.CalendarFloat, DEVSSimulatorInterface.CalendarLong, DEVSSimulatorInterface.TimeDouble, DEVSSimulatorInterface.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVSSimulatorInterface.TimeFloat, DEVSSimulatorInterface.TimeFloatUnit, DEVSSimulatorInterface.TimeLong
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DEVDESSAnimator, DEVDESSAnimator.CalendarDouble, DEVDESSAnimator.CalendarFloat, DEVDESSAnimator.CalendarLong, DEVDESSAnimator.DoubleUnit, DEVDESSAnimator.TimeDouble, DEVDESSAnimator.TimeFloat, DEVDESSAnimator.TimeFloatUnit, DEVDESSAnimator.TimeLong, DEVDESSSimulator, DEVDESSSimulator.CalendarDouble, DEVDESSSimulator.CalendarFloat, DEVDESSSimulator.CalendarLong, DEVDESSSimulator.TimeDouble, DEVDESSSimulator.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVDESSSimulator.TimeFloat, DEVDESSSimulator.TimeFloatUnit, DEVDESSSimulator.TimeLong, DEVSAnimator, DEVSAnimator.CalendarDouble, DEVSAnimator.CalendarFloat, DEVSAnimator.CalendarLong, DEVSAnimator.TimeDouble, DEVSAnimator.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVSAnimator.TimeFloat, DEVSAnimator.TimeFloatUnit, DEVSAnimator.TimeLong, DEVSRealTimeClock, DEVSRealTimeClock.CalendarDouble, DEVSRealTimeClock.CalendarFloat, DEVSRealTimeClock.CalendarLong, DEVSRealTimeClock.TimeDouble, DEVSRealTimeClock.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVSRealTimeClock.TimeFloat, DEVSRealTimeClock.TimeFloatUnit, DEVSRealTimeClock.TimeLong, DEVSSimulator, DEVSSimulator.CalendarDouble, DEVSSimulator.CalendarFloat, DEVSSimulator.CalendarLong, DEVSSimulator.TimeDouble, DEVSSimulator.TimeDoubleUnit, DEVSSimulator.TimeFloat, DEVSSimulator.TimeFloatUnit, DEVSSimulator.TimeLong

    public interface DEVSSimulatorInterface<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>
extends SimulatorInterface<A,R,T>
    The DEVS defines the interface of the DEVS simulator. DEVS stands for the Discrete Event System Specification. More information on Discrete Event Simulation can be found in "Theory of Modeling and Simulation" by Bernard Zeigler et. al.

    (c) 2002-2018 Delft University of Technology , the Netherlands.
    See for project information www.simulation.tudelft.nl
    License of use: Lesser General Public License (LGPL) , no warranty.

    $Revision: 1.2 $ $Date: 2010/08/10 11:36:44 $
    Author:
